Don't fade out on me.

34:28.930 --> 34:29.810
I know this is tough.

34:30.231 --> 34:31.152
Don't fade out on me.

34:31.232 --> 34:31.753
Bring what?

34:33.234 --> 34:35.476
All the tenth, all the tithe into the store.

34:35.777 --> 34:36.638
Circle the word all.

34:36.698 --> 34:37.619
This is important.

34:38.820 --> 34:40.121
Again, you can argue with me.

34:40.242 --> 34:41.723
You don't have to do this.

34:41.783 --> 34:44.466
This is, but I want you to least wrestle with it.

34:46.210 --> 34:48.274
Because I just believe it.

34:48.755 --> 34:49.676
He says, bring all.

34:49.757 --> 34:51.520
He doesn't say bring some or bring most.

34:51.540 --> 34:52.962
He says, bring all of the tenth.

34:53.363 --> 34:55.187
Return to me the tithe.

34:57.010 --> 35:02.260
Partial obedience is disobedience.

35:03.903 --> 35:10.034
When I've got three children and when they were younger, and I would say, Tyler, come here.

35:11.586 --> 35:14.774
And Tyler would take three steps towards me.

35:14.794 --> 35:17.159
I wasn't happy about his three steps.

35:17.280 --> 35:17.621
Why?

35:17.981 --> 35:19.144
Because what did I tell him?

35:20.127 --> 35:20.488
Come here.

35:20.949 --> 35:21.831
Come into the living room.

35:23.615 --> 35:28.146
Partial obedience is disobedience because it's about trust.

35:29.186 --> 35:30.710
That's really what this is all about.

35:31.030 --> 35:34.759
Do I believe that God's principles will actually lead to rich and satisfying life?

35:35.040 --> 35:38.709
Bring all the ties into the storehouse so there'll be enough food in my temple.

35:39.110 --> 35:43.741
The storehouse, the temple, the temple represented where God's people gathered.

35:43.761 --> 35:45.125
It represented where God was.

35:45.365 --> 35:47.410
If you were to go to the New Testament, God

35:47.586 --> 35:49.208
resides in you and me.

35:49.288 --> 35:54.074
We are as temple according to 1 Corinthians 6, but the church is where we gather together.

35:54.314 --> 35:56.497
He's not talking about your grandmother here.

35:56.817 --> 35:59.120
He's not talking about the guy on the side of the street.

35:59.360 --> 36:02.624
He's not talking about helping your nephew go to college.

36:02.945 --> 36:08.011
He's talking about returning the tithe to the local church.

36:09.413 --> 36:11.676
That's what I believe.

36:11.696 --> 36:13.518
That's what Stephanie and I practice.

36:13.538 --> 36:16.882
If you do, if you live the principal,

36:17.026 --> 36:18.027
What's the promise?

36:18.728 --> 36:20.350
I will open the windows of heaven for you.

36:20.811 --> 36:23.574
I will part a blessing so great you won't have enough room to take it in.

36:23.614 --> 36:24.175
Try it.

36:24.395 --> 36:25.536
God knew it would be tough for us.

36:26.377 --> 36:28.760
Put me to the test.

36:30.062 --> 36:30.422
All right.

36:30.643 --> 36:31.524
So that's the tithe.

36:32.645 --> 36:34.067
Secondly, we have the nudge.

36:34.367 --> 36:35.369
Second Corinthians 9.

36:35.609 --> 36:37.832
Don't give reluctantly or response to pressure for God.

36:37.852 --> 36:39.073
Loves a person who gives cheerfully.

36:39.834 --> 36:40.595
What's the nudge?

36:40.915 --> 36:46.322
It's when you see the guy on the side of the road and the Holy Spirit just kind of taps you on the shoulder and says you need to help them.

36:47.298 --> 36:48.920
It's temple sitarian.

36:49.641 --> 36:51.544
It's helping send your niece to college.

36:52.044 --> 36:53.386
It's helping your grandmother.

36:53.446 --> 36:55.188
It's taking care of your parents.

36:56.590 --> 36:58.092
It's not the tithe, it's the nudge.

36:59.114 --> 37:01.357
The tithe has nothing to do with something you feel.

37:01.417 --> 37:03.119
It has something to do with what God has said.

37:03.419 --> 37:06.123
The nudge, on the other hand, is God moving your heart.

37:07.284 --> 37:11.710
And when he does, you're either obedient or you're not.

37:12.571 --> 37:14.674
And then the other word is the word, enjoy.

37:15.170 --> 37:22.797
In other words, what is left after you've returned to God the tithe and you've been obedient when he nudges your heart.

37:22.897 --> 37:24.139
Look what it says in verse 19.

37:24.639 --> 37:28.743
Also, God gives wealth possessions and power to why.

37:28.843 --> 37:29.644
What's that next word?

37:29.724 --> 37:30.244
To do what?

37:31.465 --> 37:32.066
To enjoy.

37:32.106 --> 37:34.428
To enjoy those things.

37:34.829 --> 37:39.853
The NLT translated, it's a good thing to receive wealth from God and good health to enjoy it.

37:41.415 --> 37:44.658
God, it's just like you as a parent, what's the best part of Christmas?

37:44.962 --> 37:48.986
What you get for Christmas are watching your kids open up something they wanted so badly.

37:50.107 --> 37:52.910
Well, how much more does our Heavenly Father enjoy blessing you?

37:56.493 --> 37:56.913
He does.

37:57.614 --> 37:59.956
You say, well, Troy, I'm not being very, very blessed.

37:59.976 --> 38:01.458
The question is, are you living the principles?

38:02.839 --> 38:04.440
Have you ever asked yourself this question?

38:04.460 --> 38:07.824
It comes up, I ask myself this question, do I have too much stuff?

38:09.545 --> 38:10.866
How much is too much is a Christian?

38:11.587 --> 38:12.908
Or maybe we could put it a different way.

38:13.089 --> 38:14.610
Am I living generously?

38:15.522 --> 38:19.928
Are you a generous person, am I a generous person, a biblically generous person?

38:20.349 --> 38:22.512
Well, I think that's an easy question to answer.

38:23.373 --> 38:25.737
Here's how you answer that question.

38:26.197 --> 38:29.943
Are you returning to God a tenth of everything He's given you?

38:31.845 --> 38:33.328
Are you obedient to the nudge?

38:33.528 --> 38:39.717
When God taps you on the shoulder, do you help your knees or do you help your, whatever it is?

38:40.157 --> 38:43.442
Are you obedient to return to God the tithe

38:43.522 --> 38:48.347
the 10% of whatever he gives you, and are you obedient to the nudge?

38:48.807 --> 38:53.051
If you say, yes, I do, then you're generous according to the Bible.

38:53.792 --> 38:55.774
If you don't, you're not generous.

38:56.655 --> 38:57.656
Say, Troy, that offends me.

38:57.976 --> 38:59.558
I'm sorry, that's just what the scripture says.

39:00.098 --> 39:01.700
You might be generous according to your neighbor.

39:02.701 --> 39:08.887
You might be generous according to anyone, but you're not generous according to what the scripture has to say.

39:09.047 --> 39:12.050
You know, that's what makes talking about money in church so difficult.

39:12.994 --> 39:15.177
It's not really what does the church do with the money.

39:15.297 --> 39:15.918
You can see.

39:15.998 --> 39:18.421
You can see people's lives change, people fed.

39:18.761 --> 39:23.607
It's the fact statistically 95 to 98% of us don't do those two things.

39:26.070 --> 39:28.674
And do you ever like to be challenged on something you're not doing?

39:29.575 --> 39:30.095
I mean, I don't.

39:30.116 --> 39:31.838
You ever had somebody get up and talk about running?

39:33.280 --> 39:33.920
I hate running.

39:35.022 --> 39:37.204
And when somebody, oh, it's healthy, you ought to run.

39:37.665 --> 39:38.927
It's like, you know what I tend to do?

39:38.947 --> 39:41.650
My thing is to try to find something wrong with the person saying that.

39:42.370 --> 39:48.116
So I can say, well, if you'd fix your blah, blah, then I'd do da, da.

39:48.357 --> 39:49.438
That's why this is so difficult.

39:49.478 --> 39:52.481
Now I want us to go back to our story, and this is where we're gonna end, okay?

39:52.501 --> 39:54.163
And I'm gonna speed up, so listen quickly.

39:55.565 --> 39:59.409
But this is important, because we're going back to Jesus' teaching principles.

40:00.971 --> 40:02.252
He tells this story.

40:02.973 --> 40:10.962
He says, listen, a farmer went out to plant some seed, and as he scattered it across his field, some of the seed fell on the footpath, and birds came and ate it.

40:11.074 --> 40:14.941
Other seeds fell on the shallow soil with underlying rock.

40:14.981 --> 40:17.966
The seeds sprouted quickly because of the soil was shallow.

40:18.427 --> 40:20.871
But the plants soon withered under the hot sun.

40:21.292 --> 40:23.756
And since, because it didn't have deep roots, it died.

40:24.417 --> 40:30.387
Verse 7, Other seeds fell among the thorns and it grew up and choked out the tender plants so they produced no grain.

40:30.848 --> 40:36.498
Still other seeds fell on fertile soil and they sprouted, grew and produced a crop

40:36.738 --> 40:41.604
That was 30, 60, and even a hundred times as much as had been planted.

40:41.884 --> 40:43.466
Now, what does that story mean?

40:44.648 --> 40:45.949
What does it have to do with you?

40:47.151 --> 40:57.223
Jesus says in verse nine, anyone who has ears, hear, anyone who has ears to hear should listen and apply, listen and understand.

40:57.463 --> 40:59.826
Now, verse 10, later,

40:59.938 --> 41:07.248
When Jesus was alone with His 12 disciples and the others who gathered around, they looked at Jesus and said, what in the world does that mean?

41:08.410 --> 41:10.433
What does that story have to do with us?

41:10.813 --> 41:14.278
They didn't get it anymore than you and I do.

41:14.819 --> 41:17.122
So Jesus explains it.

41:17.723 --> 41:19.145
This is the part I want you to see.

41:19.725 --> 41:25.533
Verse 14, the farmer plants seed, taking God's word to others.

41:26.194 --> 41:28.818
That's what we have just done for the last 10 minutes.

41:29.250 --> 41:32.374
I have taken God's word, God's principles about money.

41:32.674 --> 41:34.957
Could have done it about dating.

41:35.017 --> 41:37.640
I could have done it about in any area of our lives.

41:37.820 --> 41:38.921
That's what the scripture's for.

41:39.241 --> 41:41.985
But I've taken it in an area of money and I've thrown that truth out.

41:42.966 --> 41:44.628
Not my truth, but the biblical truth.

41:44.888 --> 41:45.809
I've thrown that out.

41:46.009 --> 41:46.910
That's what he says.

41:47.451 --> 41:49.053
He says he interprets this story.

41:49.453 --> 41:53.478
The farmer plants sea taking God's word to others.

41:53.698 --> 41:55.079
So you and I are the ground.

41:55.920 --> 41:57.362
The seed is the truth.

41:58.530 --> 41:58.790
Right?

41:59.111 --> 42:02.634
And his word or me in this case is the farmer.

42:02.714 --> 42:04.055
I'm throwing that truth out.

42:04.356 --> 42:06.478
Here's how you have a rich and satisfying life.

42:06.858 --> 42:09.601
Now, what happens to it in your life and in my life?

42:10.421 --> 42:11.883
We're gonna leave it in few moments.

42:13.204 --> 42:18.049
Is your life, is my life gonna be transformed into rich and satisfying?

42:18.389 --> 42:21.512
Or a year from now, are you gonna be just as stressed about money as you are today?

42:24.455 --> 42:25.736
Well, look at what happens to it.

42:25.756 --> 42:27.858
Number one, success is stolen.

42:28.386 --> 42:30.208
And when I say success, here's what I mean.

42:30.569 --> 42:35.195
The truth, the principles to a rich and satisfying life.

42:35.896 --> 42:36.637
They're stolen.

42:36.817 --> 42:37.738
That's what the Scripture says.

42:37.778 --> 42:40.421
Look, verse 15, he's explaining this story.

42:40.762 --> 42:48.211
The seed that fell on the footpath represents those that hear the message only to have Satan come at once and take it away.

42:48.932 --> 42:49.834
Satan steals it.

42:50.474 --> 42:54.219
In other words, you're here and you hear what I said a few moments ago.

42:54.840 --> 42:56.402
You read the Scriptures.

42:57.058 --> 42:58.420
but you'll never think about it again.

42:58.460 --> 43:03.547
It doesn't penetrate your heart or your mind at all.

43:03.928 --> 43:05.630
Well, how does the enemy steal it?

43:07.433 --> 43:07.993
He lies.

43:09.415 --> 43:16.946
The moment I throw out the seed, the moment we start reading God's word, the enemy whispers in our ear and he's like, that's not true.

43:17.602 --> 43:23.708
I saw an article on Google that said, you know, and, you know, remember, it's a lie.

43:23.869 --> 43:28.233
And then he goes a step further and he'll say this, he'll say, well, okay, maybe it's true, but it's not true for you.

43:28.253 --> 43:33.579
I mean, God's not talking, he understands, you're going through a difficult time.

43:35.040 --> 43:44.370
He understands, yeah, it's true, we're supposed to be generous and yeah, it would be good if we tithe, but God understands, he's not talking, you can't afford it.

43:45.250 --> 43:47.414
You can't afford to help the guy in the size.

43:47.495 --> 43:52.625
You can't afford to return to God 10% of everything He gives you.

43:52.945 --> 43:55.110
You're struggling just to make your car payment.

43:55.491 --> 43:56.753
I want to challenge you, okay?

43:56.773 --> 44:00.040
I want to challenge you on that because I don't believe that's true.

44:01.944 --> 44:05.130
I want you to look at the shoes you're wearing and I want to ask a question.

44:05.170 --> 44:07.154
Do they make cheaper ones than the one you're wearing?

44:07.970 --> 44:10.133
Do they make cheaper shirts than the one you have on?

44:10.534 --> 44:12.637
Do they make a cheaper car than the one you drive?

44:13.018 --> 44:15.101
Do they make a cheaper house than the one you live in?

44:15.121 --> 44:22.913
I don't say that, Judge Minley, I just want you to understand that it's not you can't afford to live God's principles.

44:23.053 --> 44:26.098
It's you have chosen not to live God's principles.

44:26.499 --> 44:28.883
It's a priority decision and you can make it.

44:29.624 --> 44:30.185
It's yours.

44:30.265 --> 44:31.326
You do what you want.

44:31.667 --> 44:32.789
I'm not judging you.

44:34.692 --> 44:36.274
Listen, I believe

44:36.994 --> 44:44.705
that you do not have to live a stressful, overwhelming, scared to death, financial life.

44:46.708 --> 44:48.891
And I don't want you to miss it because you lied to yourself.

44:49.031 --> 44:51.415
If you don't believe me, you don't believe the word, that's fine.

44:52.637 --> 44:58.125
But I don't want you to miss it because the enemy steals it.

44:58.685 --> 45:01.810
The second one, success is doubted, right?

45:01.954 --> 45:02.996
Success is doubted.

45:03.436 --> 45:04.358
Mark chapter four.

45:04.398 --> 45:07.001
And again, when I say success, I'm talking about truth.

45:07.282 --> 45:10.186
I'm talking about the principles for rich and satisfying life.

45:10.466 --> 45:11.288
We begin to doubt.

45:11.348 --> 45:12.229
Isn't that really true?

45:12.249 --> 45:13.050
Can't look what he says.

45:13.190 --> 45:13.972
Jesus' words.

45:14.312 --> 45:17.116
The seed on the rocky soil represents those who hear the message.

45:17.677 --> 45:23.105
They receive it with joy, but since they don't have deep roots, they don't last long.

45:23.566 --> 45:27.952
They fall away as soon as they have a problem or are persecuted for believing God's word.

45:28.413 --> 45:29.394
So you hear

45:29.794 --> 45:30.315
the truth.

45:30.375 --> 45:33.421
You heard what the Scripture said a few moments ago when it comes to money.

45:33.742 --> 45:36.728
And you're like, yeah, I believe that.

45:36.768 --> 45:38.892
I believe I can have a rich and satisfying life.

45:39.193 --> 45:41.076
And I believe I can do it.

45:41.617 --> 45:42.840
I can return to God.

45:43.140 --> 45:44.563
I know it won't satisfy me.

45:44.663 --> 45:45.806
I know it's not reliable.

45:46.026 --> 45:48.050
And I'm going to be generous according to the Scripture.

45:50.338 --> 45:55.545
And you do for two weeks, man, you make $100, you give, return to God 10.

45:55.606 --> 45:59.651
And God nudges your heart to help the person in line at Starbucks and you help them out.

46:00.813 --> 46:06.181
But then you get a flat tire or the car's kids get sick and things get financially tight.

46:06.601 --> 46:07.563
You get under pressure.

46:07.583 --> 46:08.284
That's what it says.

46:08.324 --> 46:09.265
You get persecuted.

46:10.487 --> 46:11.168
And what happens?

46:12.389 --> 46:13.651
What does this scripture say?

46:14.472 --> 46:15.634
Our roots,

46:16.226 --> 46:18.349
Don't go very deep, so we doubt.

46:18.609 --> 46:19.370
And what is doubt?

46:19.470 --> 46:23.335
Doubt is the enemy of faith, right?

46:24.076 --> 46:36.031
And when we doubt, what happens is we're like, ah, well, God, we go back to what we used to, God understands I can't this week, I will next week, or I can't now, I will later.

46:36.291 --> 46:38.834
And you know that was you, it dried up.

46:40.162 --> 46:42.886
You say, I've tried this in the past, Troy, it didn't work.

46:42.946 --> 46:44.428
No, it's not that it didn't work.

46:44.749 --> 46:45.309
It's at what?

46:45.730 --> 46:48.394
Our roots didn't go deep enough.

46:48.414 --> 46:52.039
How, when our roots go deep, our faith is fed.

46:52.119 --> 46:53.261
How do we feed our faith?

46:54.543 --> 46:59.810
Well, according again to the scripture, one of the ways we do it is by hanging out with God.

47:01.373 --> 47:06.420
Praying, talking to God, reading His word 10, 15 minutes a day, consistently.

47:06.440 --> 47:07.922
That's why I talk about it.

47:09.538 --> 47:12.683
I don't get paid according to how much Bible you read.

47:12.703 --> 47:19.735
I talk about reading the Bible because it will feed your faith because you will be persecuted financially.

47:19.755 --> 47:26.006
And what I mean is you're going to go through times when it is financially tight and tough.

47:27.368 --> 47:30.674
How else do we grow our faith by being faithful to his house?

47:32.066 --> 47:33.308
You didn't come up with church.

47:33.388 --> 47:34.369
I didn't come up with church.

47:34.750 --> 47:37.574
God did in His Word that we are to gather together.

47:37.694 --> 47:37.995
Why?

47:38.195 --> 47:47.609
So your faith will be fed so that when you are tempted or when you doubt the principles, you won't stop living them.

47:49.752 --> 47:57.424
So as to not have a rich and satisfying life, you know, Steph and I have been through a lot in our lives.

47:57.504 --> 48:00.408
I've had encephalitis, didn't know who I was.

48:00.929 --> 48:01.650
I've had

48:02.210 --> 48:04.293
Bell's palsy where my face drops down.

48:04.353 --> 48:05.815
I've had stents put in my heart.

48:06.315 --> 48:18.991
I mean, we know what it's like to take wick, to get milk for Tyler, to take, have Raymond Noodles because, you know, going down to Exxon is all we can afford.

48:19.672 --> 48:27.022
But through all those things, we had a deep faith to trust God and say, God, we're going to keep trusting you.

48:27.402 --> 48:30.386
And he took care of us through those things.

48:30.626 --> 48:35.431
Even in the midst of those things, we were able to have a rich, hopeful, peaceful life.

48:36.152 --> 48:40.077
But about 2007, 2008, several things happened.

48:40.137 --> 48:44.481
One is my heart started giving me trouble, and I had stents put in.

48:45.663 --> 48:52.470
Now for 20 years, the 20 years before that, I had gotten up at five o'clock every morning, or let's say five, six days a week.

48:53.612 --> 48:57.035
And I'd hung out with God, and then I had been at the gym by 6 a.m.

48:57.856 --> 48:59.378
I was very careful about what I ate.

49:00.834 --> 49:05.060
It didn't seem right that I would be the one with blockage in my arteries.

49:08.265 --> 49:12.912
Also, when we moved here, we prayed for friends because we didn't know anybody.

49:13.573 --> 49:14.855
And God gave us some friends.

49:15.055 --> 49:17.999
One couple we got very close with for 10 years.

49:19.502 --> 49:25.631
And then they left the church in a very hurtful situation.

49:25.651 --> 49:26.832
I didn't understand it.

49:26.993 --> 49:30.578
I still hurt today over that situation.

49:31.874 --> 49:33.055
There was an opportunity.

49:33.075 --> 49:41.906
You know, from the time I was in college, I read a book a week, I listened to conferences, I sacrificed to go to a conference.

49:41.926 --> 49:44.209
I did everything I knew to do to grow professionally.

49:44.630 --> 49:48.274
And there was this one opportunity that I really wanted and it didn't happen.

49:48.735 --> 49:50.316
And it was usually discouraging to me.

49:50.717 --> 49:55.703
And if you remember, 2007, 2008 was also when the financial crisis hit.

49:56.644 --> 50:01.490
And our mission here of launching churches and campuses got incredibly difficult.

50:01.794 --> 50:09.806
The financial struggle, even to this day, has been incredibly challenging, which is difficult.

50:10.367 --> 50:13.511
Well, all those other things never impacted my doubt.

50:13.792 --> 50:14.393
This did.

50:14.413 --> 50:21.423
It's like, man, are the principles true?

50:22.585 --> 50:23.346
Can you trust it?

50:25.602 --> 50:30.527
If you do this, this, I mean, if I live what God says I live, will He keep His word to me?

50:30.547 --> 50:31.789
Will He keep His promise to me?

50:34.372 --> 50:46.565
Now, I'm thankful for all those years of building deep roots so that while that doubt was around the edges of our lives, we didn't surrender to it.

50:50.489 --> 50:51.650
But we all have to face it.

50:53.913 --> 50:55.154
That's why I plead with you.

50:55.394 --> 51:01.481
That's why I challenge you to be committed in those areas of your life.

51:02.402 --> 51:03.463
Let me give you these last two.

51:05.566 --> 51:08.008
Jesus says success is not prioritized.

51:08.769 --> 51:20.082
In verses 18 and 19, he says, the seed that fell among the thorns represent others who hear God's word, but all too quickly the message is crowded out by the worries of life, the lure of wealth.

51:20.162 --> 51:21.445
the desire of other things.

51:21.505 --> 51:22.406
So no fruit is produced.

51:22.427 --> 51:23.248
This is not the roots.

51:23.268 --> 51:24.190
This is the thorns.

51:24.531 --> 51:26.074
This is once you get a blessing.

51:27.336 --> 51:29.941
You start your own company, you start making money.

51:31.505 --> 51:33.629
And you know what the thorns are?

51:33.909 --> 51:34.571
What does it say?

51:35.192 --> 51:36.274
You want more.

51:38.338 --> 51:41.743
And now you have this wrestle within yourself.

51:41.983 --> 51:42.864
You want more.

51:42.924 --> 51:47.210
You like this blessing and you want more of it.

51:47.250 --> 51:51.897
So you start to desire it and your desire for more crowds out what?

51:52.257 --> 51:53.198
Chokes out what?

51:53.819 --> 51:55.722
Your willingness to lift the principles.

51:57.905 --> 51:59.147
My blessing can be dangerous.

51:59.187 --> 52:03.092
Did you know the more money somebody makes, the less generous they are?

52:03.813 --> 52:04.594
Percentage wise?

52:05.506 --> 52:08.110
The more God blesses somebody, the more they hang on to.

52:08.390 --> 52:09.732
See, they say things like this, why?

52:09.752 --> 52:13.156
I'm giving more than most people, dollar amount.

52:13.637 --> 52:15.540
But God's not concerned about the dollar amount.

52:15.560 --> 52:17.823
He didn't give us principles with the dollar amount.

52:17.863 --> 52:19.185
You won't find it anywhere in scripture.

52:19.485 --> 52:21.969
He gave us, percentage why?

52:22.009 --> 52:24.893
Because he's after our heart.

52:24.913 --> 52:25.433
Last one.

52:26.094 --> 52:27.977
And this is the one I want for you.

52:28.578 --> 52:31.762
I want it for me and I want it for our church.

52:33.922 --> 52:39.589
And I don't know any other way of you and me and our church experiencing this than to live His principles.

52:39.609 --> 52:40.230
Look what it says.

52:40.850 --> 52:42.112
And the seed, the truth.

52:42.713 --> 52:57.831
Those principles fell on good soil, represents those who hear and accept God's work, and produces a harvest of 30, 60, and even a hundred times as much as been planted.

52:59.213 --> 53:00.434
That's what God wants for you.

53:02.370 --> 53:04.273
but ultimately you have to make the choice, don't you?

53:05.976 --> 53:06.377
We all do.

53:07.919 --> 53:12.547
We all have to do something with the seed that gets thrown onto our heart.

53:13.208 --> 53:13.909
Let me pray for us.

53:14.390 --> 53:15.812
Father, I pray that you'd be with us.

53:18.076 --> 53:29.394
And I pray, God, I pray that we would all experience a rich and satisfying life, that we'd be able to trust your word and your character and your faithfulness.

53:31.650 --> 53:32.851
Ask it in Jesus' name.

53:34.172 --> 53:34.473
Amen.

53:35.354 --> 53:36.214
Let's give God a hand.

53:36.274 --> 53:36.755
Can we do that?

53:42.500 --> 53:43.001
All right.

53:43.341 --> 53:44.722
I'm gonna ask our ushers to come.

53:45.143 --> 53:46.604
Gonna have an opportunity, I guess.

53:46.945 --> 53:48.586
You might say, to apply.

53:48.626 --> 53:57.214
The coach in me is always gonna give you an opportunity to respond to whatever we have learned, or at least whatever we've talked about.

54:00.057 --> 54:01.138
Let me pray for our giving.

54:08.546 --> 54:12.009
God, it's so easy to know things that are hard to do.

54:14.111 --> 54:27.044
And whether it be in our business life or our parenting life, our married life, in this case, our financial life, the enemy's good at what he does.

54:27.965 --> 54:30.927
Help us to have faith in you.

54:31.948 --> 54:33.510
I pray God for everyone here.

54:33.570 --> 54:37.714
I pray for those who are struggling the most, who have

54:37.794 --> 54:46.182
who have this great weight on them, who love you and wanna please you, but scary.

54:47.964 --> 54:53.790
All the only place I know to turn is to your word, and I just ask that you would do in their lives what you had promised to do.

54:54.351 --> 54:55.772
When we're weak, you are strong.

54:56.173 --> 54:57.614
Your grace is sufficient.

54:58.595 --> 55:01.998
That's what your word says, and that's what we trust in Jesus' name.

55:03.440 --> 55:05.522
Let's give together, all right, as we worship.

